            <person xml:id="pers1645">
               <p>From non-conformist roots, Potter aligned with the Church of
                     <placeName>England</placeName> on entering University College,
                     <placeName>Oxford</placeName> in <date when="1688">1688</date>. He went on not
                  only to be ordained in the Church of <placeName>England</placeName> but to serve
                  as Bishop of <placeName>Oxford</placeName> (<date from="1715" to="1737"
                     >1715–37</date>) and Archbishop of <placeName>Canterbury</placeName> (<date
                     from="1737" to="1747">1737–47</date>). He interacted with the Wesley brothers
                  several times in these roles, including ordaining <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> both deacon and priest. See
                     <hi rend="italic">Alumni Oxonienses</hi>; and <hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi>.</p>
            </person>
